Moreover, the transactions in the said bank account remained unrecorded in the books of accounts, hence resulting to incomplete accounting records and lack of audit trail contrary to Section 112 of Presidential Decree No. 1445.

a. Closely monitor the utilization and implementation of priority projects for the attainment of desirable socio-economic development and to maximize the usage of the fund;

b. Provide additional manpower in the MEO in order to fast track the implementation of pending projects. Meanwhile, consider implementation of projects “by Contract” since the management does not have enough manpower to implement projects “by Administration”;

c. Fast track the implementation based on the scheduled time frames indicated in the AIP by the implementing department concerned to achieve the desired management outcomes; and

d. Strict compliance with the provisions of Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-1 of the Department of Interior and Local Government and Department of Budget and Management dated April 13, 2011 should be observed.

We recommended that management through the municipal accountant :
Submit SEF Annual Budget and Quarterly Utilization Reports to the office of the Audit Team Leader concerned;
Book up expenses incurred with appropriate accounts as provided under Unified Accounts Code Structure (UACS);
Support all the disbursements with appropriate and complete documentation to avoid future audit suspensions and disallowances and
Strict adherence with the provisions of the above-mentioned criteria is highly enjoined.
